<p><b>You don't need to be a designer to make a web app easier to use.</b></p>
<p>Successful web apps are usable web apps. The better an app's usability the more paying users you get, the happier customers and clients you have. But how can a dev team make web apps more usable?</p>
<p>Over the last 20 years as both a developer and UX designer, I've developed a technique that non-designers can use to improve the usability of the web apps they build.</p>
<p>I've used the technique in the design and construction of many apps with thousands of users and hundreds of usability tests with real people from all walks of life. The technique always works.</p>
<p>In this book, a fast read with lots of examples, you'll quickly learn the technique and be able to immediately apply it to your work. I call it Normal UI.</p>
