<section class="container">
  <h2>What Do We Mean By "Normal" UI?</h2>
  <p>We don't mean "normal" as in normal or abnormal. The term is inspired by database normalization, where database tables are normalized or denormalized.</p>
  <p>We define UI in your web app as normalized or denormalized. Your UI for a particular sequence of tasks is either normalized (spread across many screens) or denormalized (the user stays on one screen).</p>
  <p>That simple concept is surprisingly effective at defining ways to improve web app usability under particular circumstances. Sometimes you want a normalized interface. Sometimes you want a denormalized one. The book will show you when and how to do so.</p>
</section>
